dct_title_s: Alger. Algeria. Alger and vicinity (uncontrolled mosaic)
dct_description_sm: United States. Army Map Service. Depth of sea shown by contour lines on upper portion of map. N.W. Africa Zone grid. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Map is 3 of 7 sheets. Sources: uncontrolled mosaic by the Army Map Service, 1942 and aerial photography by R.A.F.. 1942. The Map Library does not have the rest of the set. On verso: "New York: West Point and vicinity: Grid Zone 'A' " (1:29,000), as both an aerial photograph and a topographic map.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1942.
